In the final analysis of the norming study, in the syntactically congruent condition, we evaluated 72 pairs that scored above 5.8 points as semantically congruent pairs, and 72 pairs that scored below 3.85 points as semantically incongruent pairs. For the syntactically incongruent condition, we evaluated 72 pairs that scored above 5.1 points as semantically congruent pairs and 72 pairs that scored below 3 points as semantically incongruent pairs. To ensure control over variables, we regulated target word frequency in terms of semantic congruency (congruent/incongruent), syntactic congruency (congruent/incongruent), PVF, and TVF [F(1, 288) = 0.101, p = 0.751, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
