The semantic priming effect for words was assessed using two distinct measurements and described in Fig. 2. The initial measurement, denoted as XO-OO, involved the subtraction of RTs in the OO condition (semantically and syntactically congruent) from those in the XO condition (semantically incongruent yet syntactically congruent). This measurement allowed us to isolate the influence of semantic congruency between the prime and target while maintaining syntactic congruency. To evaluate the semantic priming effect ascertained by this first measurement across different visual fields, a two-way rm-ANOVA was conducted for each participant. The factors considered were the PVF (LVF/RVF) and the TVF (LVF/RVF). The analysis yielded no significant main effect for PVF [F(1, 59) = 0.427, p = 0.516, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
